.TH XVA-TOOL 1 "June 2026" "v1.0.0" "XvaTool Core Manual"
.SH NAME
xva-tool \- High-Performance Zero-Copy XenServer Streaming Orchestration Utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xva-tool
[\fB\-q\fR] [\fB\-f\fR] [\fB\-r\fR] [\fB\-R\fR] [\fB\-\-throttle\-mb\fR=\fIMB/s\fR] \fIsubcommand\fR [\fIarguments\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B xva-tool
is a stream-driven processing framework designed to optimize the extraction, validation, and conversion of virtual machine disk images stored inside uncompressed XenServer XVA container formats.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quiet
Muffle system telemetry line updates inside the terminal window.
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-force
Bypass all interactive barriers, executing non-interactive permission loops.
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-resume
Engage block-level sector appending resumption checks on the output image file descriptor.
.TP
.B \-R, \-\-rescue
Engage a non-destructive bad-sector handling routine to bypass hardware read drops.
.TP
.B \-\-throttle\-mb=\fIMB/s\fR
Enforces an administrative bandwidth constraint limiting sequential write throughput. Default is 0 (unlimited).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B info \fIarchive\fR
Extracts and validates primary XML hypervisor configuration tables.
.TP
.B merge \fIarchive\fR \fItarget\fR
Processes and collapses sparse disk layer sequences into a continuous flat RAW target volume.
.TP
.B verify \fIarchive\fR
Executes an integrity allocation sweep across the container structure.
